# Project Context

PocketHost is a **multi-tenant PocketBase hosting platform** (monorepo). Core pieces:

- **`packages/pockethost`** — Node CLI and services (mothership, edge daemon, firewall, instance lifecycle)
- **`packages/dashboard`** — SvelteKit marketing site and user docs
- **`packages/pockethost-instance`** — Docker image for per-instance PocketBase containers
- **`mothership-app`** — PocketBase control-plane app (hooks, migrations, handler APIs)

Stack: TypeScript (ESM), Commander CLI, Express, Docker, PocketBase JS client, pnpm workspaces.

Read [MEMORY.md](MEMORY.md) before substantive architectural work.

Mothership hook code (`mothership-app/src/lib/handlers/`) runs in PocketBase Goja JSVM after tsdown bundling. Read [.cursor/rules/mothership-hooks.mdc](.cursor/rules/mothership-hooks.mdc) before adding imports or shared helpers.

# Programming Style

- Prefer factory functions that return an API object instead of classes (`createX`, `mkX` — matches existing code)
- Prefer early returns
- Match surrounding file conventions (imports via `@` alias in `packages/pockethost`)

# Generating Markdown

- When proposing an edit to a markdown file, first decide if there will be code snippets in the markdown file.
- If there are no code snippets, wrap the beginning and end of your answer in backticks and markdown as the language.
- If there are code snippets, indent the code snippets with two spaces and the correct language for proper rendering. Indentations level 0 and 4 is not allowed.
- If a markdown code block is indented with any value other than 2 spaces, automatically fix it

# Generating code — command guardrails

Avoid side-effectful or long-running operations unless the user explicitly asks:

- **Do not** start hosting services (`mothership`, `firewall`, `edge:daemon`, `serve`) — they spawn Docker instances and bind ports.
- **Do not** run full production builds (`dashboard` vite build, Docker image build/push) or deploy (`wrangler pages deploy`).
- **Do not** run `tsc` / `svelte-check` unless the user asks — use targeted reads and local reasoning instead.
- **OK**: `pnpm lint` / Prettier, read-only git commands, file edits, one-off non-server scripts.
